BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by the Council of Ministers' General Secretariat] </F>
  [Text] In view of the Israeli treacherous aggression and 
the victims in al-Biqa', Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri held 
talks with President Ilyas al-Hirawi and Chamber Speaker Nabih 
Birri. At the end of the meeting, it was decided to declare 
Friday, 3 June 1994, a day of official mourning in honor of the 
martyrs who fell victim in the dreadful massacre. 
  In condemnation of this grotesque crime, the public and 
private establishments, universities and schools will be closed 
tomorrow to emphasize the Lebanese people's legitimate right to 
resist the occupation and in assertion of Lebanon's sovereignty 
on all its territories. 

